					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Given that the low bit resolution of NES audio output, it wouldn't be hard to recover bit-perfect output from the NES. The only snag is that it runs at a 1.79 MHz sampling rate, so you'd need a video ADC to capture it. And there's not much you could do with it that would make sense; you'd either feed it back to a DAC, or downsample it to 44.1/48/96 kHz.</div>

